ABUJA – The Minister of Transportation, Mu’azu Jaji Sambo, is bereaved following the untimely demise of his younger brother, Ja’afaru Jaji Sambo. Eric Ojiekwe, the Ministry’s Director, Press and Public Relations in a statement noted that the sad event occurred on Monday,18th July 2022. Friends and well-wishers described Ja’afaru as a quintessential gentleman, a master strategist, a philanthropist, a loyalist, a family man, a dependable friend, and above all devoted Muslim”. He was an embodiment of what the Jaji Sambo brothers represent which differentiates them from others: Decorum, philanthropism, respect, sincerity, and team spirit. It was further disclosed that he was sponsoring well over 300 students from Jalingo Local Government before his demise. The Management and staff of the Federal Ministry of Transportation sympathise with the Minister of Transportation, in this moment of grief and pray to the Almighty Allah (SWT) to grant him Jannah.